 potential work to continue the evolution\nand push for a wide adoption of the H-SON paradigm. More importantly, as a key\n6G architectural feature we propose that H-SONs should be loosely coupled\nnetworks. Loose coupling refers to the weak interaction of different layers and\nweak interaction between users in the same layer, i.e., the various feedback\nloops must be almost isolated from each other to improve the stability and to\navoid chaotic situations. We finally conclude the paper with the key hints\nabout the future landscape and the key drivers of 6G H-SONs.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 17 Dec 2021 21:15:39 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 16 Jan 2023 11:44:58 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-01-18"}
